lat_ratio= float(airports[airports['city']==nn].latitude)/float(Bermuda['A'])

# Now lets rescale the data.
data.loc[:,'A'] *= lat_ratio
data.loc[:,'B'] *= lon_ratio
# sort the dataframes for the next step
data.sort_values('A',inplace=True)
airports.sort_values('latitude',inplace=True)
In [10]:
import folium
# Get a basic world map.
airports_map = folium.Map(location=[30, 0], zoom_start=2)
# Draw markers on the map.
i=0
k=0.01
for _, row in data.iterrows():
    latitude=row['A']
    longitude=row['B']
    found=False
    #We will try and get the airport name from airports dataframe, which can be used as a pop-up
    while True:       
        if (abs(airports.iloc[i]['latitude']-latitude)<k and abs(airports.iloc[i]['longitude']-longitude)<k):
            found=True
            Name=airports.iloc[i]['name']
        if airports.iloc[i]['latitude']>latitude:
            break
        i+=1
    if not found:
        Name="---"
    
    folium.Marker(location=[latitude, longitude],popup=Name).add_to(airports_map)
# Save the mapas html
airports_map.save('airports.html')
airports_map
